The paper deals with 3D object retrieval using deep learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM) sub-categories. The use of contrastive loss and clustering for optimization suggests a focus on optimization and learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The retrieval aspect of the paper suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Lastly, the use of deep learning techniques and optimization for better performance suggests an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
